args:
Saint Starfall... The one who hands
presents out on Dragonyule.
And now that I've undertaken such duty,
I shall see it through to completion.
Who is next on my list, pray?
Ah, wonderful. They are all assembled\nin the selfsame location.
Now that I have donned this garment,\nthere is but one thing I must do...
The gifts from Saint Starfall must all find\ntheir way into your possessions!
Er, that means it's present time, right?\nWooo! Presents! Gimme, gimme!
Patience, sirrah, lest you corrupt the\nmoment! You will have your gift anon.\n...Ah, yes. There it is.
Oh man, what's it gonna beeee?
Whoooa, this is a premium bowstring!
Man, I wish EVERY day was Dragonyule.
It gladdens me to see you so happy.\nNext, I have a gift for Ranzal.
Eh, I'm too old for this kinda stuff...\nThough since yer here, what the hell!\nNow, what'd ol' Saint Starfall bring?

Sweet mother'a crap! This is one'a those
crazy rare mushrooms—most people write
'em off as make believe, but anyone who
finds one swears they're delicious!
You seem much satisfied, Ranzal.\nI pray this finds a choice spot upon\nyour next banquet table.
No complaints here. Thanks a million!
Next, I've something for Elisanne.\nIn truth, this was far and away the most\ndifficult gift to acquire.
Well, I am quite looking forward to it.\nWhat is it?
'Tis the novel you were much desirous of.\nThe one which fell under the genre of\nromanc—
THANK YOU NEFARIA I ACCEPT IT GLADLY!
You seem rather...intense about that\ngift, Elly. Why is that?
Gah! N-no reason at all, Your Highness!\nPay me no mind!
N-now, Nefaria! Give His Highness his gift!\nYes, that would be perfect.
My apologies, but I am still worrying\nover what manner of gift to procure\nfor the prince.
I fear I must go above and beyond,\ngiven his relative import.
Huh? Nonsense. Just get me something\nnice like you did with everyone else.
Nay, that is unacceptable! A rare and\nextraordinary man such as yourself\ndeserves a gift of equal weight.
Prithee, might I ask you to wait until I find\na token which adequately gives form to my\ngratitude for all that you do?
My darling and everyone else look to\nbe having ever so much fun...\nI see now what Dragonyule is all about!
That being said...where is MY present,\nNefaria?!
Ah yes. Of course. This is for you.
AUGH! It's a plushie of my sweet darling!\nOh, it is simply ADORABLE!
This is truly the best present ever.
And lastly, a gift for Cleo.\nI pray you do not find it wanting.
Er, a gift for me? But as you can see,\nI am also Saint Starfall right now.
That means I hand out presents,\nnot receive them.
Oh, I think it's okay. Let's not get hung\nup on rules if it means everyone gets\nto have a good time.
He speaks sooth. Now take this, I beg.
Ah! It is a kitchen knife and cookpot!\nGoodness, look at the keen edge on\nthis blade...
When last I espied you in the scullery,\nI noticed your cookware was quite\nworn indeed.
I pray you find these items to your\nsatisfaction.
This is quite impressive, Nefaria.\nYou put thought into everyone's gifts,\nright down to the smallest...
No, this will never do. I must be allowed\nto give Nefaria a present in return for\nthose she has given us!
You are part of the castle family now,\nwhich means you also deserve to be\nhappy on this day!
Hey! I wanna make her happy too!
Same. Ain't my style to just keep getting\nwithout givin' in return.
If we're all decided, then let us set\nabout selecting the perfect gift for her.
...Thank you all. However, your thoughts\nalone are more than satisfactory.
There is nothing that I require.
(Will I never be able to have it?\nNo matter how much I may desire it...?)
I was recalling something from the past.\nMy memories of those times are dim,\nand yet...there WAS something.
Something I most desperately desired,\nand yet could not obtain.
Then let's try to figure out what this\nmystery thing is!
Alas and alack, I have not a clue even\nwhere to begin such a search.
Good thing we have Saint Starfall\non the case.
Right then—we'll figure out the special\nsomething Nefaria wanted and find a\nway to make it happen!
Ah, but you are boon companions all...
So be it. I look forward to your gift.
